The paper deals with designing a dynamic data structure for monitoring the acceptance of a word by a fixed automaton as symbols are revealed one at a time. This involves processing symbols interleaved with timestamps, which suggests a connection to timed automata. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper focuses on designing a data structure for the monitoring problem. The paper also involves complexity analysis, which suggests a connection to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper deals with automata theory, which suggests a connection to cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
